We should set the Windows file version on the SDK installer so that it is possible to right-click on the installer and find out what the version number is.  Since we don't change the name based on version number, it is difficult to know which version you have.

&lt;b&gt;- Where are we today?&lt;/b&gt;
The Windows SDK installer does not have Windows file version information.

&lt;b&gt;- Why is this a problem?&lt;/b&gt;
It is hard to determine what version a particular Windows SDK installer is without going through the process of installing it.

&lt;b&gt;- The proposed enhancement:&lt;/b&gt;
Add the SDK version as an fie attribute to the installer
